tice\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.hyndburnbc.gov.uk/borough-council-elections-2020/ |title=Hyndburn Borough Council - elections 2020|accessdate=March 10, 2020 |work=The Hyndburn Borough Council}}</ref>. Approximately one third of the local council's 35 seats would have fallen up for election on that day<ref name=\"TEC-Notice\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.electoralcommission.org.uk/who-we-are-and-what-we-do/elections-and-referendums |title=Elections & Referendums - what we do |accessdate=March 7, 2020 |work=The Electoral Commission}}</ref>\n\nAdditionally, on the same day, the election<ref name=\"PCC-Election\">{{Cite web|url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_England_and_Wales_police,_fire_and_crime_commissioner_elections/ |title=2020 England and Wales PCC elections |accessdate=March 7, 2020 }}</ref> for Police and Crime Commissioner for the Lancashire Constabulary area<ref name=\"2020-England-and-Wales-PCC-Election\">{{Cite web|url=https://whocanivotefor.co.uk/elections/pcc.lancashire.2020-05-07/police-and-crime-commissioner-for-lancashire-constabulary/ |title=Who Can I Vote For - Lancs. P.C.C. Election |accessdate=March 7, 2020 }}</ref> would also have been held on Thursday 7 May 2020.\n\nUPDATE # On Friday, March 13th, the UK Government announced that ALL May-elections<ref name=\"MAY-Elections-Cancelled\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-51876269/ |title=BBC - Coronavirus: English local elections postponed for a year |work=BBC News |date=13 March 2020 |accessdate=March 13, 2020 }}</ref> will be postponed for a year, in response to the ongoing Coronavirus: outbreak.\n\n{{TOC limit|3}}\n\n==Background==\nBefore the (Postponed) election [[Labour Party (UK)|Labour]] had a majority of 26 councillors, [[Conservative Party (UK)|Conservatives]] had 9 councillors<ref name=\"HBC-Councillors\">{{Cite web|url=https://democracy.hyndburnbc.gov.uk/mgMemberIndex.aspx?FN=PARTY&VW=LIST&PIC=0 |title=Hyndburn Borough Council - Your councillors by political party |accessdate=March 7, 2020 |work=The Hyndburn Borough Council}}</ref>\n\nLabour would have been defending 10-seats with Conservatives defending 2-seats.\n\nAs a result, the composition of the council's 35 seats will remain UNCHANGED, until elections are re-scheduled, due in May 2021 (TBC) -\n\n*[[Labour Party (UK)|Labour]] 26\n*[[Conservative Party (UK)|Conservative]] 9\n\nNB: Four (of 16) Council wards, where seats would NOT have been up for re-election in 2020, included the following wards - Clayton Le Moors, Huncoat, Immanuel in Oswaldtwistle and Milnshaw in Accrington. However, as there was ALSO an election for Lancashire's next Police and Crime Commissioner, polling stations in those Four wards would have ALSO been OPEN.\n\nPrevious Councillors who were looking to Stand-Down in the May 2020 election included - Tony Dobson (Con) (Barnfield), Stephanie Haworth (Lab) (Overton)\n\nUPDATE #  Sadly, Councillor Tony Dobson (Con) (Barnfield), suddenly died on Monday, March 30th - as such his seat will probably by left 'vacant' as no by-elections will be called during the Coronavirus 'Lockdown'.\n\n==Ward Councillors==\n\nElected in May 2016, these Ward Councillors were expected to serve just a full FOUR-YEAR term, but will be required to serve another 12-Months, until the Postponed elections have been re-scheduled, due in May 2021 (TBC).\n\n===Altham===\n{{Election box begin | title=Altham}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link|\n  |party      = Labour Party (UK)\n  |candidate  = Steve BUTTON\n  |votes      = 0\n  |percentage = 0.0\n  |change     = -0\n}}\n{{Election box end}}\n\n===Barnfield===\n{{Election box begin | title=Barnfield}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link|\n  |party      = Conservative Party (UK)\n  |candidate  = Tony DOBSON\n  |votes      = 0\n  |percentage = 0.0\n  |change     = -0\n}}\n{{Election box end}}\n\n===Baxenden===\n{{Election box begin | title=Baxenden}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link|\n  |party      = Conservative Party (UK)\n  |candidate  = Terence Keith HURN\n  |votes      = 0\n  |percentage = 0.0\n  |change     = -0\n}}\n{{Election box end}}\n\n===Central===\n{{Election box begin | title=Central}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link|\n  |party      = Labour Party (UK)\n  |candidate  = Abdul Ghafar KHAN\n  |votes      = 0\n  |percentage = 0.0\n  |change     = -0\n}}\n{{Election box end}}\n\n===Church===\n{{Election box begin | title=Church}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link|\n  |party      = Labour Party (UK)\n  |candidate  = Jean BATTLE\n  |votes      = 0\n  |percentage = 0.0\n  |change     = -0\n}}\n{{Election box end}}\n\n===Netherton===\n{{Election box begin | title=Netherton}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link|\n  |party      = Labour Party (UK)\n  |candidate  = Noordad AZIZ\n  |votes      = 0\n  |percentage = 0.0\n  |change     = -0\n}}\n{{Election box end}}\n\n===Overton===\n{{Election box begin | title=Overton}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link|\n  |party      = Labour Party (UK)\n  |candidate  = Stephanie HAWORTH\n  |votes      = 0\n  |percentage = 0.0\n  |change     = -0\n}}\n{{Election box end}}\n\n===Peel===\n{{Election box begin | title=Peel}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link|\n  |party      = Labour Party (UK)\n  |candidate  = Paddy SHORT\n  |votes      = 0\n  |percentage = 0.0\n  |change     = -0\n}}\n{{Election box end}}\n\n===Rishton===\n{{Election box begin | title=Rishton}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link|\n  |party      = Labour Party (UK)\n  |candidate  = Jeff SCALES\n  |votes      = 0\n  |percentage = 0.0\n  |change     = -0\n}}\n{{Election box end}}\n\n===Spring Hill===\n{{Election box begin | title=Spring Hill}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link|\n  |party      = Labour Party (UK)\n  |candidate  = Munsif DAD\n  |votes      = 0\n  |percentage = 0.0\n  |change     = -0\n}}\n{{Election box end}}\n\n===St. Andrew's===\n{{Election box begin | title=St. Andrew's}}\n{{Election box candidate with party